<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910521-0145</DOCNO><DOCID>910521-0145.</DOCID><HL>   Technology Brief -- Microsoft Corp.:   Software Package to Simplify   Writing `Windows' Programs</HL><DATE>05/21/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   MSFT</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>SOFTWARE (SOF)</IN><RE>WASHINGTON (WA)</RE><LP>   Microsoft Corp., Redmond, Wash., announced a softwarepackage that seeks to simplify a programmer's task of writingsoftware that runs on Microsoft's popular Windows program.   Microsoft's new package, Visual Basic, allows a programmerto write software using a language similar to Basic, apopular programming language, and to include Windows featuresin those programs. Windows, a &quot;graphical user-interface&quot;program, provides any software written to run on Windows withfeatures such as onscreen boxes and &quot;icons,&quot; or symbols, thata computer user can manipulate using a &quot;mouse&quot; pointingdevice.</LP><TEXT>   Visual Basic will speed programming time, Microsoft said,because it simplifies the process by which programmers chosethe Windows components that will appear in their programs.Microsoft said it will begin shipping Visual Basic, which hasbeen widely reported on in the trade press, in June. Theprogram will list for $199, Microsoft said.</TEXT></DOC>